 But I mean to say - that's because I had a different - I was brought up with a - with a kind of a religious family but - swearing was taboo and children were not - thought they used to hear their parents swear - it was a thing that they - kept their chil
d
ren from. I mean to say children pick up bad language - children, even today, as soon as they hear something that's not right they pick it up. And - my mother - if I said anything that was wrong, she never said anything, she never - don't you say that, be
