\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Well - those who'd got money by - by right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 What do you mean right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
Well inherited. They was very good. If you - if you - now in the country that was more - more significant in the country than it was in town, because - in the country you'd have the Lor
d of the Manor, and he would have his - he would be able to have his footmen, his grooms, and that, and he always retreated - they was always a good class gentleman in those days - taught his children to - treat you, the groom, with respect. If he -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 You used to see this when you stayed in Kent?
