\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Well the landlord for a start off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Did you see much of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Yes, he used to come - no, you never saw much of the landlord, you see his agent. B
ecause he daren't come round in some places the landlord himself daren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 What did you think of the landlord in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Well they was - they were - they could be very very naughty, they could turn you out in the street. If you never paid you
r rent all they'd got to do was to send the bailiffs in and out would go your blooming furniture, lot in the street, lock stock and barrel. And nobody would pity you either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 How did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Well - 'cos couldn't do nothi
ng about it, there was no redress, you couldn't - if you didn't pay your rent well that's your fault for not paying your rent. The only thing you used to do was to - make a moonlight flit and - find somewhere else to live so he couldn't catch you up.

