\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Do you remember feeling as a boy that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Oh yes, you knew your parents had to struggle. You knew and you never - you never - what shall I say, never - aggravated the situation.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 What did you think about it as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
Well you accepted it 'cos it - that was the - that was the general - atmosphere in those days. Everybody was the same, we never worried about it, you never worried about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Did you ever need to get help from the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 You - oh it's no 
good going to the parish, one of the things that they wouldn't go to. The parish - the Board of Guardians they used to call 'em, Board of Guardians. And - if you - called in the Board of Guardians they used to come and visit you and if you had a piano in 
y
our blooming house, that was the lot mate, you had to sell that before they - ever thought of giving you anything. I mean to say that was a means test in it's - in it's - filthiness and - it was ugly. Anything - anything - that - appeared to be - you know
 - comfortable - got to get rid - what do you want - what do you - what do you mean, keeping that lovely mantel }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8024667\charrsid11078316 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316  over}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8024667\charrsid11078316  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
mantel over your mantelpiece. Sell it. If you want money you can't expect money when you've got - stuff like that, get rid of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Did your family ever have to have the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
No. No. No. Lot of people used to - used to rather starve than go to the R,O, what they call the R.O's. They'd sooner go without than go - be little themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Where there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Well they was - they was - sent to Coventry such people you see, all - that's all there was to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Do you ever remember anything called rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
Oh - oh that was a common occurrence on Saturday night 'cos the pubs used to keep open 'til about twelve o'clock at night so you always had your -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 I mean actually to get rid of someone, neighbours ganging up on someone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Well, no, I wouldn't like
 to - I - I couldn't say because we never - never indulged in anything ourselves so was never - I was never - in - you know, engaged in anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Were you given any lessons before you went to school at all by parents or anyone at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 How old were you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
Well I wouldn't know but I know I told you, I think I told you I paid about sixpence a week to go to a church school, I think it was about sixpence, it may not have - been so much but - I 
know we had to pay to go to school at church school. But that was only for a little while, soon afterwards they fetched in the - would it be - would it be the Educational Act, where everybody was compelled to go to school? They started building school - t
hen I - soon after I'd been to that church school I was sent - another school in the district called Spurling Road and from there I went onwards. Elementary schools they was called in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Do you remember much about the first school you were at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Yes, that was the first school I went to was Spurling Road school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Did you go there all day to begin with or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 I come home to dinner, used to have your - your - your - your dinnertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Do you remember what the hours were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
No, I - no, I suppose they wasn't - they - I suppose it was say - nine o'clock to - well, they used - they used to ring the old bell you know, used to be a bellringer }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8024667\charrsid11078316 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316  care}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8024667\charrsid11078316 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
taker'd ring a bell and - I suppose it went about nine o'clock you see then - p
laytime when - you had your playtime. You had - and I'll tell you what, there was - those teachers in those days - were - absolutely - cared for their pupils. Some of 'em didn't, there was some of 'em there - they knew a child who hadn't had no breakfast.
 
They could sense a child - then when they break time come they used to - used to give 'em something, you know, something to eat, they used to - go out and buy something. And you - you - you'd see this teacher share - have a little bit extra for the child 
w
ho'd had nothing. Because the teachers in those days knew the poor. Knew the poor, they was - with the poor all the time, and they knew how - a child would suffer because it's parents had - hadn't - some of the children'd go to school without any breakfas
t.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 What sort of things did the teachers emphasise, did they emphasise manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
Manners and everything, you see, they used to - they used to - do what they do now I suppose, try to educate you and some had - some had their own peculiar
 ways of educating you but - they - educated the - I was - I was - pretty well satisfied with my education at school. They was - it was a plain - education, it was a bread and - bread and butter education you had in those days, no frills attached to it. W
e
 - we went in algebra but - it was only - you never - delved into languages or anything like that, you - you delve - it was more of a bread and butter education you got in those days, and the teacher used to - know that the - it's no good teaching a child
 
who was going out to work as soon as he was fourteen any - anything extra because - he knew it was able - he wouldn't have been able to - exercise his knowledge would he. He had - there was after - there was evening classes. But people were - and it was, 
y
ou know, taken advantage of - by the people who were a little bit better off. If - if you could earn a living and that was the first thing they thought, of the economic situation - in those days was so - great that you had to - you had to utilize everythi
n
g you could have, every child, if he could earn - a penny, well you - you - you - took advantage of it. Not because the parents - now I - I believe I told you my parents - sent me out to work as soon as I was fourteen. Now, not because they was callous. B
e
cause the economic situation, you - was so great and they had to - use me as a source of income. Well - at school in those days - even the - Government realized the fact - if - a widow say - for a start off had a couple of sons and - the school leaving ag
e
 was fourteen, you could go and ask for an exam - labour exam and pass - leave school at thirteen. Provided - they used to give you intelligence test. See, and if - if you passed the standard of the intelligence test you could leave school at thirteen. So
 that's how the economic situation was for children in those days, even the Government - realized you was a - a source of income for parents.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 How long were you at the Spurling Road school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Oh well - when we moved - when you moved - if you moved you went to another area. You - you went to another school, nearer to you.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Which school did you go to after the Spurling Road one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Well I think I - I - I think I stopped at Spurling Road school for most of me life. Schooldays really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
Oh you get - you get the cane, you know, I mean to say the - the teacher ruled, the teacher ruled the class, he had to. He had to, to - to keep discipline, - there was no like - there was 
no - there was no - there was no - point in having a lot of rebels in your class you would never teach 'em - anything. Cane was the - the deterrent. Punishment was a deterrent and they could punish and all in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Was it a mixed school, girls and boys?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Some of 'em were, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 The one you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 No, we had boys and girls, though I was in a boys class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 So there were boys and girls at the school but they were in separate classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 But separate classrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Do you - know if they gave the girls the cane or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
Oh I wouldn't know, I shouldn't know, I never - I never heard my sister complain to me. I know they did the boys, whether they did the girls I wouldn't know. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
Oh yes, they used to be proud, I mean to say I - I - if - I used to get my prize - for progress and - regular attendance, I used to come home with a - book - for - you know it was marked by the headmaster, presented for - progress a
nd regular attendance and show your mum she was quite proud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Did the parents ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
No, there was no - no - no parents days in those days. No. I wouldn't know not because - not the - boarding - called board schools, not the board
 schools, elementary board - I wouldn't know whether that happen - whether it happened in the - the - or the grammar schools in those days, whether it - that happened I wouldn't know, I never went to one so I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Did the other children at Spurling Road come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
Everybody was on the same level, but - there was some - areas - were a little bit more affluent, you could put it that, I don't think the word affluent was - generally used in those days. 
But - there was some areas that were more affluent than others, for instance - if you had a boy in your class come from - Lansdowne Road that's 'picking out a road that I know, I - Lansdowne Road, there was all big houses there. Never had no servants but 
t
hey was big houses but - evidently they must - their father's must have had a better job. And a regular income you see, they may have been - policemen or firemen who would - anybody with a regular income - anybody with a regular income - was better off th
a
n - other people, there's no doubt about it there was a distinction between people who had regular income - regular jobs. There was never on short time or anything like that. So they had a constant - wage, which was better than a high wage really. So you 
c
ould cater for - from one - from the beginning of January to the end of - Christmas - during the - December, you knew what was coming in, but other people didn't know whether was coming in one week more than the other you see, so - that'd be a bit dicey. 
S
ee? So those people lived in a - what we call a - better class neighbourhood, put it that way. And if you had a - classmate - a boy - a classroom boy in your house come from - Lansdowne Road and you say, cor he - he - he's father is a posh bloke I know yo
u
 see. But - that's how we used to - you see, be some people come from a poor home and a - they were - used to be mixed but - they used to - try and get - if they had a little bit extra money used to try and go to private schools if they could. But - that 
didn't always happen you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Oh yes, if you was a smart lad you was - you was made - you was made - you was made monitor. I'll tell you - did I tell you p
reviously that I was - we used - I used to be a bellboy. In a tennis club. Well - you - I was a bellboy because I was a monitor. I had more, shall we say - go, put it that way, than the others you see, some of 'em didn't trouble. They knew they'd got to g
o
 out to work well they didn't care a tinker's cuss whether they - learnt anything or not. Some of 'em - never learnt anything and didn't want to. There was no - there was - wasn't looked down upon, that was one of the - looked upon as a part of the - life
 in those days, if you never learnt anything, some people never went to school - at all, they used to dodge it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Oh there were groups. Yes, there were groups, they used to hang about corners. Groups. Well to avoid those areas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 What were they based on, were they one the streets or areas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
No, in the road, they kept to their own road you see anybody walking down their road was - well you - you avoided those roads, there was - I can - I - I can v
isualize now a number of roads that was really - where people would gang up on you. So you avoided those areas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Other boys would gang up on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Yes. I say you used to avoid 'em. 'h yes, I - I know quite a number of roads that used to be - avoid
ed by anybody that didn't to get - in a rough house. Oh yes, there was rough houses in those days. But it wasn't stabs or anything like that, it was a - it was a punch up. A real punch up. And they - they - they may some}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12520229\charrsid11078316  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 there you in treacle or something like that just to - make it uncomfortable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 You left school at fourteen, would you have stayed any longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Oh I never thought of it, we never thought of it, nobody ever thought of it. There were very few - there were 
people who kept after school but - I wouldn't know, my parents and my - the general - the general public, the poor - the general working class families, you went out to work as soon as you reached fourteen. You went - and the girls - the girls and the boy
s went out to work, - that was all their - that was their outlook, go to work. The economic situation - that was our outlook, the economic situation - was so great that you had to go out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
You couldn't because I - when I went to work - when - after - when I went to work - when I went to work, I worked from six o'clock in the morning 'til six o'clock at night - in the summertime. Eight 'til eight in the winter. Now the winter time was - was 
the time when - the evening classes started. Well you - you just fancy - boys working 'til eight o'clock at the night, the time they came home they didn't want to go to - evening classes. So it was only the privileged - there was a lot of people did have 
i
t, but only those who - fortunate - very very fortunate. Not in my - not in - I don't suppose anybody in my - who worked in a factory went. No, I would say not - there may be the odd - odd person out in the general - practice, once you went home you went 
- you stopped at home. Then you went to bed because there was no lights on, there was no electricity in those days, it was all paraffin lamps and candles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Yes, I do because I often think - that - I may have been - a better - I may have reached a higher - pin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12520229\charrsid11078316 na}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
cle in me trade. You see, I had to learn the hard way. That had one advantage, if you learn the hard way you never forget it. I learnt the hard way and it wasn't 'til - later on that I became any 
- able to take charge of anybody, which I did in the finish. But it was only because - it was only - it was only too late in life to - to have had the advantage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Do you think you benefited from the schooling you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Well I knew full well that I
 - I - I used to - I used to - make me own education, I tell you what I used to - study - there was - crossword puzzles were coming out late - later on, the crossword puzzles were coming out and all that sort of thing. Well I used to study them to find ou
t
 the meaning of the words you see and that - that enlarged my - yes, and my - knowledge of words and what the meaning of works were. That - that increased it a lot, I used to use that - very very often. And I - actually I - I was a - people used to ask me
, what's the meaning of so and so? And I was able to tell 'em because I'd studied these crosswords.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 You told me you had lots of part time jobs or ways of earning a little money while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 You told me about the ball}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16476657\charrsid11078316 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 boy and cleaning knives and forks, were there any others you used to do, oh and selling newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10358713 SB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 
Oh I sold newspapers, anything that I could - I used to sell newspapers, I used to sell - programmes at the - football programmes at the Spurs ground. Anything where there was a copper or two - to be gained I used to do it. Run errands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Did you used to find these jobs yourself?
