hat sort of thing and I walked out. She never said nothing to me but she told this - Mr Randall that I went home at five to - I forget now what it was - I was home a bit earlier and I never never asked if there was anything else I could do. So he said, yo
u - you don't study me, I can't study you, you'd better go and get another job. So I went to Levis' and got - apprentices at Levis'.
