n - for an Ingersoll watch, pocket watch. Cor luv a duck, that Ingersoll pocket watch, I wind it up about every ten minutes. Oh I was chuffed, I was showing everybody my mother had bought me a - Ingersoll watch, 'cos Ingersoll's watches were - they was ma
de in America. And then they got an Ingersoll firm over here now but - first of all they was fetched over from America and they was - quite a good watch for half a crown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7218946 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15817354\charrsid11078316 Did you remember anything about holidays with pay or anything?
